parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump assembly can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: cracks in the fuel pump housing or fuel tank flange.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause a significant loss of braking performance, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The brake failure light comes on
the motorcycle has little to no braking power
the brakes feel soft or spongy
the motorcycle is difficult to stop

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump Housing Cracks Causing Gasoline Leaks
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracks in the plastic fuel pump housing can cause gasoline leaks, which can lead to fires or explosions, especially when in close proximity to ignition sources such as the starter and alternator.
symptoms: fuel flowing from the cracks in the fuel pump housing
